The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       The City Diary
                A man was killed and two were injured in three road accidents on Tuesday. A 65-year-old pedestrian, who is yet to be identified, was injured when a minibus collided with a taxi near the Strand Road-Fairley Place intersection around 4pm on Tuesday. The man was pronounced dead at Medical College and Hospital. Pedestrian Madhumanti Ghoshal, 17, was injured when a bus plying on route 3B hit a motorcycle on JM Avenue near Shyambazar around 11.15am. She was taken to RG Kar Hospital. The driver and the motorcyclist were arrested. Around 3.40pm, Asha Devi, 45, was hit by a minibus at the Rabindra Sarani-Vivekananda Road crossing. She was taken to Medical College and Hospital. The driver was arrested.     Mrinal Sen was released from the Calcutta Medical Research Institute on Tuesday. He was admitted on July 25 and underwent prostate surgery the next day.     Power supply maybe affected in Anandapur, Madurdaha, Kalikapur, Jagatipota, Mukundapur, Rajpur, Purbadiganta, Purbalok, Ajaynagar and Manasloke, on the southern fringes, between 10am and 3pm on Wednesday because of CESC maintenance work.    A truck driver and his two helps were killed when the vehicle hit a house beside NH6 at Jorakaltala in Uluberia around 10.30am on Tuesday.    Two people were attacked with a chopper following a clash between CPM and Trinamul Congress supporters on Dent Mission Road in Watgunge on Tuesday evening. The incident took place when Trinamul supporters allegedly ransacked a nearby CPM party office. A police team rushed to the spot and brought the situation under control. No one was arrested.    Train services were disrupted in the Bandel-Katwa section of Eastern Railways Howrah division on Tuesday afternoon when a group of passengers blocked trains at Jirat station demanding a new train on the route.     Ruchira Bantira, 19, was injured after she rammed her Maruti Esteem into a railing along Lindsay Street while driving out of the parking plaza around 3.40pm on Tuesday. A hawker was also injured. Both were taken to SSKM Hospital. Ruchira, a resident of Harish Mukherjee Road, was shifted to a nursing home. The car was impounded.    Mohammed Azad, 20, was arrested from Mominpore on Tuesday afternoon on the charge of being involved in an arms racket. A loaded revolver was found on him.              
